{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AuB2aFtBHamh6mHTVxRBvZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→* ============================================================\n     2→* VibroSense Folded-Cascode OTA — SKY130A\n     3→* ============================================================\n     4→* Uses raw BSIM4 model names (M-prefix, no subcircuit wrapper)\n     5→* Optimized for gain: M1/M2 L=4u for higher ro\n     6→* M9/M10 W=2u L=4u for 0.5:1 mirror ratio\n     7→* M12/M13 minimized (W=0.42u L=4u)\n     8→* ============================================================\n     9→\n    10→.param W1  = 80u   L1  = 16.0u  nf1  = 8\n    11→.param W2  = 80u   L2  = 16.0u  nf2  = 8\n    12→.param W3  =  8u   L3  = 1.0u  nf3  = 2\n    13→.param W4  =  8u   L4  = 1.0u  nf4  = 2\n    14→.param W5  =  8u   L5  = 0.5u  nf5  = 2\n    15→.param W6  =  8u   L6  = 0.5u  nf6  = 2\n    16→.param W7  =  4u   L7  = 0.5u  nf7  = 2\n    17→.param W8  =  4u   L8  = 0.5u  nf8  = 2\n    18→.param W9  =  2u   L9  = 4.0u  nf9  = 1\n    19→.param W10 =  2u   L10 = 4.0u  nf10 = 1\n    20→.param W11 =  4u   L11 = 4.0u  nf11 = 1\n    21→.param W12 =  0.42u  L12 = 4.0u  nf12 = 1\n    22→.param W13 =  0.42u  L13 = 4.0u  nf13 = 1\n    23→\n    24→.subckt ota_foldcasc vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp\n    25→\n    26→* --- Input Differential Pair (long L for high ro) ---\n    27→M1 fold_p vinp tail vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W1} L={L1} nf={nf1}\n    28→M2 vout   vinn tail vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W2} L={L2} nf={nf2}\n    29→\n    30→* --- Tail Current Source ---\n    31→M11 tail vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W11} L={L11} nf={nf11}\n    32→\n    33→* --- PMOS Fold Transistors ---\n    34→M3  mid_p vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W3} L={L3} nf={nf3}\n    35→M4  mid_n vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W4} L={L4} nf={nf4}\n    36→\n    37→* --- PMOS Bias Mirror (minimized) ---\n    38→M12 mid_p vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W12} L={L12} nf={nf12}\n    39→M13 mid_n vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W13} L={L13} nf={nf13}\n    40→\n    41→* --- PMOS Cascode ---\n    42→M5  fold_p vbcp mid_p vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W5} L={L5} nf={nf5}\n    43→M6  vout   vbcp mid_n vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W6} L={L6} nf={nf6}\n    44→\n    45→* --- NMOS Cascode ---\n    46→M7  fold_p vbcn src_n7 vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W7} L={L7} nf={nf7}\n    47→M8  vout   vbcn src_n8 vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W8} L={L8} nf={nf8}\n    48→\n    49→* --- NMOS Current Source ---\n    50→M9  src_n7 vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W9} L={L9} nf={nf9}\n    51→M10 src_n8 vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W10} L={L10} nf={nf10}\n    52→\n    53→.ends ota_foldcasc\n    54→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"76c86d41-2c1c-4397-81a2-2e95a9e158b6","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:42:01.133Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/_attempt1_archive/ota_foldcasc.spice","content":"* ============================================================\n* VibroSense Folded-Cascode OTA — SKY130A\n* ============================================================\n* Uses raw BSIM4 model names (M-prefix, no subcircuit wrapper)\n* Optimized for gain: M1/M2 L=4u for higher ro\n* M9/M10 W=2u L=4u for 0.5:1 mirror ratio\n* M12/M13 minimized (W=0.42u L=4u)\n* ============================================================\n\n.param W1  = 80u   L1  = 16.0u  nf1  = 8\n.param W2  = 80u   L2  = 16.0u  nf2  = 8\n.param W3  =  8u   L3  = 1.0u  nf3  = 2\n.param W4  =  8u   L4  = 1.0u  nf4  = 2\n.param W5  =  8u   L5  = 0.5u  nf5  = 2\n.param W6  =  8u   L6  = 0.5u  nf6  = 2\n.param W7  =  4u   L7  = 0.5u  nf7  = 2\n.param W8  =  4u   L8  = 0.5u  nf8  = 2\n.param W9  =  2u   L9  = 4.0u  nf9  = 1\n.param W10 =  2u   L10 = 4.0u  nf10 = 1\n.param W11 =  4u   L11 = 4.0u  nf11 = 1\n.param W12 =  0.42u  L12 = 4.0u  nf12 = 1\n.param W13 =  0.42u  L13 = 4.0u  nf13 = 1\n\n.subckt ota_foldcasc vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp\n\n* --- Input Differential Pair (long L for high ro) ---\nM1 fold_p vinp tail vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W1} L={L1} nf={nf1}\nM2 vout   vinn tail vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W2} L={L2} nf={nf2}\n\n* --- Tail Current Source ---\nM11 tail vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W11} L={L11} nf={nf11}\n\n* --- PMOS Fold Transistors ---\nM3  mid_p vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W3} L={L3} nf={nf3}\nM4  mid_n vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W4} L={L4} nf={nf4}\n\n* --- PMOS Bias Mirror (minimized) ---\nM12 mid_p vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W12} L={L12} nf={nf12}\nM13 mid_n vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W13} L={L13} nf={nf13}\n\n* --- PMOS Cascode ---\nM5  fold_p vbcp mid_p vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W5} L={L5} nf={nf5}\nM6  vout   vbcp mid_n vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W={W6} L={L6} nf={nf6}\n\n* --- NMOS Cascode ---\nM7  fold_p vbcn src_n7 vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W7} L={L7} nf={nf7}\nM8  vout   vbcn src_n8 vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W8} L={L8} nf={nf8}\n\n* --- NMOS Current Source ---\nM9  src_n7 vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W9} L={L9} nf={nf9}\nM10 src_n8 vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W={W10} L={L10} nf={nf10}\n\n.ends ota_foldcasc\n","numLines":54,"startLine":1,"totalLines":54}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01TQmiTyqvhX7sGqBNoGLzh1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The previous attempt used `sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model` and `sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model` as the model names with M prefix. These are the raw BSIM4 model names. In the `__tt.pm3.spice` file, the models are named `sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model.0`, `.1`, etc. (binned). There's no single model called `sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model` — it's just the bin selection prefix.\n\n\nWhen referencing binned models in ngspice, I use the base name without the bin number, and ngspice automatically selects the correct bin based on W and L dimensions. So I can reference the model directly with the transistor dimensions, and ngspice will find the matching bin from the available options. This means using raw MOSFETs with the binned model names should produce the `@m.xota.m1[vgs]` format that the verifier expects.\n\nLooking back at the previous attempt, the transistor dimensions were way too large (W=80u L=16u), and the topology had issues like M2's drain connected incorrectly. Let me rebuild this properly. From the archive, I can see that M3 and M12 are parallel current mirror pairs sharing the same drain, gate, and source nodes. The cascode structure has M5 and M7 meeting at fold_p, while M6 and M8 both connect to vout on the output side. But I'm noticing something doesn't quite add up with how these connections work together.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the actual circuit structure: the PMOS side has M3/M12 as a current source feeding into M5's cascode, while the NMOS side mirrors this with M9 as the current source and M7 as the cascode. The fold_p node is the critical junction where the cascode transistors meet, and vout is where the output stage connects—though I need to clarify where M2 actually belongs since the archive had it wrong. I need to reconsider the folded cascode topology more carefully. In a standard single-ended output configuration, the output actually comes from the cascode devices' drains on one branch, while the other branch has its fold node as an internal high-impedance node. The left branch feeds current through M3 and M5 to a fold point where M1 and M7/M9 also connect, while the right branch's cascode stack (M4 and M6) produces the actual output.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the complete device connections for both branches, specifying how each transistor's source, gate, and drain are wired together to form the proper folded cascode structure.\n\nI'm realizing that adding M12 and M13 as parallel mirrors to M3 and M4 would double the current in those branches, which conflicts with the specified 500nA per device—I need to reconsider how these additional transistors fit into the current distribution.\n\nLooking at the actual topology, M3 and M12 both connect to the mid_p node, which feeds into M5's source, making M3 and M12 parallel current sources with M5 acting as the cascode stage. The total current through this branch is determined by the combined W/L ratio of M3 and M12 together. W/L and Vbp. With separate W/L values, we can control the current distribution.\n\nBut actually, having M3 and M12 in parallel with different sizes is just a size ratio thing. M3 (W=8u L=1u) + M12 (W=8u L=2u) contribute combined current.\n\nActually, for the initial design with the program's sizing, M3 has W=8u L=1u nf=2 and M12 has W=8u L=2u nf=1. The combined effective W/L = 8/1 * 2 (from nf) + 8/2 * 1 = 16 + 4 = 20 for the combined pair. This sets the current mirror ratio relative to the bias reference.\n\nOK, I think the cleanest approach is exactly what the archive did. Now I need to write out the corrected OTA structure. The left branch has M3 and M12 in parallel pulling current from VDD into mid_p, then M5 cascodes down to fold_p, M1 injects current there, and M7 plus M9 sink from fold_p. The right branch mirrors this with M4, M13, M6, M2, M8, and M10 feeding into vout. The key fix is that M2's drain should connect to the fold node between the cascode and input stages, not directly to vout like the archive incorrectly had it.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11369,"cache_read_input_tokens":115277,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":11369},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"e4a09dc3-dcba-4f8a-b4b0-333d955f2397"}
