{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016qHQCqazQQ8HgtNNYjygDX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So with the subcircuit approach, the reference is `@m.xm1.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vgs]`. But the verifier expects `@m.xota.m1[vgs]`.\n\nNow, if the OTA is instantiated as `Xota`, and inside the OTA subcircuit, the device is `XM1` (subcircuit instance of sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8), then the full reference would be:\n\n\n`@m.xota.xm1.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vgs]`\n\nThe verifier pattern expects `@m.xota.m1[vgs]`, which means the MOSFET must be a direct M-device with the binned model, not an X subcircuit instance. So I need to use M-prefix devices, but the binned model base name isn't resolving properly. Let me dig into why that's happening.\n\nI'm wondering if the `.pm3.spice` file has a different model definition structure, or if the dot in `.model sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model.0` is causing issues—in ngspice, the dot acts as a bin separator, so the base model is `sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model` with bin numbers `0`, `1`, etc. For auto-binning to work, the W and L dimensions of my M-device need to fall within the lmin/lmax/wmin/wmax range of exactly one bin. Let me check if W=10u L=1u matches the first bin's range of lmin=20nm to lmax=100nm.\n\nSince L=1u is below the 20nm minimum, bin 0 doesn't match—I need to find which bin actually covers L=1u.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":884,"cache_read_input_tokens":145074,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":884},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"1df3c1a1-c200-4f4b-9abe-45e9da5a3a37"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016qHQCqazQQ8HgtNNYjygDX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019JAEWz1wDYcKhNcrj1DbM8","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"# Find which bin matches W=10u L=1u\ngrep -B1 \"lmin.*lmax.*wmin.*wmax\" /home/ubuntu/pdk/sky130A/libs.ref/sky130_fd_pr/spice/sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__tt.pm3.spice | grep -A1 \"model\\.\" | while IFS= read -r line; do\n    if echo \"$line\" | grep -q \"model\\.\"; then\n        bin=$(echo \"$line\" | grep -o 'model\\.[0-9]*')\n    fi\n    if echo \"$line\" | grep -q \"lmin\"; then\n        lmin=$(echo \"$line\" | grep -o 'lmin = [0-9e.+-]*' | awk '{print $3}')\n        lmax=$(echo \"$line\" | grep -o 'lmax = [0-9e.+-]*' | awk '{print $3}')\n        wmin=$(echo \"$line\" | grep -o 'wmin = [0-9e.+-]*' | awk '{print $3}')\n        wmax=$(echo \"$line\" | grep -o 'wmax = [0-9e.+-]*' | awk '{print $3}')\n        echo \"$bin: L=[$lmin, $lmax] W=[$wmin, $wmax]\"\n    fi\ndone | head -20","description":"Find bin ranges"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":884,"cache_read_input_tokens":145074,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":884},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"d08385c9-cf1a-4a1f-a076-85429c8f0c72"}
