{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VcGVdsG9UovY3mCGtChTQo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NSBtRvmrS8XaAVFyx5c9jM","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/debug.spice << 'EOF'\n* Test even smaller PMOS for 500nA at Vov > 150mV\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\n\n* Test M3 alone: W=0.84u L=4u nf=1\nVbp1 g1 0 dc 0.5\nVd1 d1 0 dc 1.2\nXM3a d1 g1 vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.84u L=4u nf=1\n\n* Test M3 even smaller: W=0.42u L=4u nf=1\nVbp2 g2 0 dc 0.5\nVd2 d2 0 dc 1.2\nXM3b d2 g2 vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=4u nf=1\n\n.dc Vbp1 0.40 0.75 0.01 Vbp2 0.40 0.75 0.01\n.op\n* Just do a single op with Vbp at the point where Vov=150mV (Vbp=0.65)\n.control\nalter Vbp1 dc = 0.65\nalter Vbp2 dc = 0.65\nalter Vd1 dc = 1.2\nalter Vd2 dc = 1.2\nop\nlet id1 = abs(@m.xm3a.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[id])\nlet id2 = abs(@m.xm3b.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[id])\nlet vov1 = (abs(@m.xm3a.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vgs]) - abs(@m.xm3a.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vth]))*1000\nlet vov2 = (abs(@m.xm3b.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vgs]) - abs(@m.xm3b.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vth]))*1000\necho \"W=0.84u L=4u: Id=$&id1*1e9 nA  Vov=$&vov1 mV\"\necho \"W=0.42u L=4u: Id=$&id2*1e9 nA  Vov=$&vov2 mV\"\n\n* Now try at Vbp = 0.60\nalter Vbp1 dc = 0.60\nalter Vbp2 dc = 0.60\nop\nlet id1b = abs(@m.xm3a.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[id])\nlet vov1b = (abs(@m.xm3a.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vgs]) - abs(@m.xm3a.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vth]))*1000\necho \"W=0.84u L=4u @ Vbp=0.60: Id=$&id1b*1e9 nA  Vov=$&vov1b mV\"\nquit\n.endc\n.end\nEOF\n/usr/bin/ngspice -b debug.spice 2>&1 | grep -E \"W=|nA\" | head -10","description":"Test smaller PMOS at Vov=150mV point"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4191,"cache_read_input_tokens":161138,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tok