t be with the convergence. Let me try adding `.nodeset` or `.ic` to help with the operating point.\n\nWait, let me verify that Vss is actually at 0V—the voltage source definition `Vss vss 0 dc 0` sets node `vss` to ground potential, and when I instantiate the OTA, that `vss` node maps to the subcircuit's ground reference. But I'm wondering if there's a naming conflict since ngspice is case-insensitive and I'm using `Vss` for both the source name and `vss` for the node. Let me try renaming the voltage source to avoid any ambiguity.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2776,"cache_read_input_tokens":176757,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2776},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"4f0cbbe3-1799-4aa1-bc13-c1f6bfe20893"}
