{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VWUtANiNNY4o4vwJgnJapS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"At 250nA (diode-connected):\n\n| Device | W | L | Vgs | Vth | Vov (mV) |\n|--------|---|---|-----|-----|---------|\n| XN1 | 2u | 0.5u | 0.560 | 0.633 | -73 |\n| XN2 | 0.42u | 0.5u | 0.627 | 0.613 | +14 |\n\n\n| XN3 | 0.84u | 0.5u | 0.605 | 0.640 | -36 |\n\nThe narrower device at 0.42u finally gives positive overdrive voltage, though still modest at 14mV. I'm noticing threshold voltage varies significantly across widths at this fixed length—0.42u has the lowest Vth at 0.613V while 0.84u jumps to 0.640V, suggesting I need to explore this width dependency more carefully to find the sweet spot for positive Vov.\n\nTo achieve 50mV overdrive with the 0.42u device, I'd need to push Vgs to 0.663V, which would drive the current up to around 630nA based on the exponential relationship I'm seeing in the diode measurements. That's problematic because in the folded cascode topology, M7 and M9 must carry the same current, so if M9 is biased at 250nA, forcing M7 to 630nA creates a significant mismatch that breaks the circuit's symmetry.\n\nTrying longer channel lengths doesn't help much either—extending L to 1u only gets me to about 45mV at 250nA, still short of the 50mV target. The constraint is extremely tight: I need the NMOS devices in the signal path to maintain overdrive above 50mV while staying within the current budget the circuit allows. mV at 250nA with W=0.42u L=1u is borderline. If I bump M7 to 300nA with the same dimensions, I get Vov≈60mV which clears the 50mV threshold. Let me work out the current budget: M11 tail at 600nA drives M1 and M2 at 300nA each, M9 and M10 also at 300nA, and the PMOS branches at 600nA per side, totaling 1.2µA from supply to ground. For the mirror ratio between M9/M10 and M11, I need 0.5, which means M9 gets W=2u L=4u.\n\nNow checking the PMOS side: I need 600nA per branch with Vov exceeding 150mV, and from the M3 characterization data at 250nA with W=0.42u L=1u I'm right at the edge—bumping to 300nA gives me the headroom I need.\n\nFor the cascode pair M5/M6, I'm verifying that W=0.42u L=2u can handle 300nA while maintaining adequate overdrive voltage, and the numbers are tracking as expected. Vbcn needs to be higher than 0.88V to keep M7 in saturation with sufficient overdrive, but increasing it will push the output voltage up, which creates a tension in the design that I need to resolve.\n\nLet me try Vbcn = 0.90V, which gives Vgs_M7 = 0.70V and Vov = 70mV—that works. Now I'm setting Vbp = 0.72V for the PMOS branches and working through Vbcp to establish the fold_p voltage around 1.4V.\n\nFor M5 to have sufficient overdrive, I need Vsg > 1.09V, which means Vbcp should be below 0.31V. Rather than keep iterating on these bias points, I'll just run the simulation to see how close I am. I've adjusted the transistor dimensions—keeping most at 0.42u width with varying lengths, scaling up M9/M10 and M11 for the current mirrors, and using longer channels for M12/M13 to improve matching.\n\nNow checking the bias voltages: Vbn=0.59V, Vbcn=0.90V, Vbp=0.72V, and Vbcp=0.30V look reasonable. With M7/M8 at W=0.42u L=1u, I'm getting around 60mV overdrive at 300nA, which should work.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":923,"cache_read_input_tokens":226395,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":923},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"f045658c-39da-4410-99c7-57bb8bf83d0b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VWUtANiNNY4o4vwJgnJapS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GWMWMz2uZ5cPMdRuM8H6Yz","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/ota_foldcasc.spice << 'EOF'\n* VibroSense Folded-Cascode OTA — SKY130A v3\n* All devices sized for Vov constraints at nA currents\n\n.subckt ota_foldcasc vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp\n\n* Input Pair (W=0.42u L=1u, ~300nA each → Vov≈60mV)\nXM1 fold_p vinp tail vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=1u nf=1\nXM2 fold_n vinn tail vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=1u nf=1\n\n* Tail (~600nA)\nXM11 tail vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=4u L=4u nf=1\n\n* PMOS Fold (W=0.42u L=1u, ~545nA at Vov=160mV)\nXM3  fold_p vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=1u nf=1\nXM4  fold_n vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=1u nf=1\n\n* PMOS Bias Mirrors (very small ~55nA)\nXM12 fold_p vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=8u nf=1\nXM13 fold_n vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=8u nf=1\n\n* PMOS Cascode (W=0.42u L=2u, ~300nA at Vov≈175mV)\nXM5  cas_p vbcp fold_p vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=2u nf=1\nXM6  vout  vbcp fold_n vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=2u nf=1\n\n* NMOS Cascode (W=0.42u L=1u, ~300nA → Vov≈60mV)\nXM7  cas_p vbcn src7 vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=1u nf=1\nXM8  vout  vbcn src8 vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=1u nf=1\n\n* NMOS Current Sources (~300nA, ratio 0.5 of M11)\nXM9  src7 vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2u L=4u nf=1\nXM10 src8 vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2u L=4u nf=1\n\n.ends ota_foldcasc\nEOF\n\ncat > /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/debug.spice << 'EOF'\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd nvdd 0 dc 1.8\nV0 ngnd 0 dc 0\nVbn nbn 0 dc 0.59\nVbcn nbcn 0 dc 0.90\nVbp nbp 0 dc 0.72\nVbcp nbcp 0 dc 0.30\nVinp ninp 0 dc 0.9\nVinn ninn 0 dc 0.9\n\nXota ninp ninn nout nvdd ngnd nbn nbcn nbp nbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL nout 0 10p\n\n.nodeset v(nout)=0.9 v(xota.fold_p)=1.4 v(xota.fold_n)=1.4\n.nodeset v(xota.cas_p)=0.9 v(xota.tail)=0.25 v(xota.src7)=0.15 v(xota.src8)=0.15\n\n.op\n.control\nrun\n\n* Print all devices in compact format\necho \"DEV     | Id(nA)  | Vgs    | Vth    | Vov(mV) | Vds    | Vdsat  | Sat?\"\necho \"--------|---------|--------|--------|---------|--------|--------|-----\"\n\n* M11\nlet id = @m.xota.xm11.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[id]*1e9\nlet vgs = @m.xota.xm11.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vgs]\nlet vth = @m.xota.xm11.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vth]\nlet vov = (vgs-vth)*1000\nlet vds = @m.xota.xm11.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vds]\nlet vdsat = @m.xota.xm11.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vdsat]\necho \"M11     | $&id | $&vgs | $&vth | $&vov | $&vds | $&vdsat\"\n\n* M1\nlet id = @m.xota.xm1.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[id]*1e9\nlet vgs = @m.xota.xm1.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vgs]\nlet vth = @m.xota.xm1.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vth]\nlet vov = (vgs-vth)*1000\nlet vds = @m.xota.xm1.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vds]\nlet vdsat = @m.xota.xm1.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vdsat]\necho \"M1      | $&id | $&vgs | $&vth | $&vov | $&vds | $&vdsat\"\n\n* M3 (PMOS - use abs)\nlet id = abs(@m.xota.xm3.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[id])*1e9\nlet vgs = @m.xota.xm3.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vgs]\nlet vth = @m.xota.xm3.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vth]\nlet vov = (abs(vgs)-abs(vth))*1000\nlet vds = abs(@m.xota.xm3.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vds])\nlet vdsat = abs(@m.xota.xm3.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vdsat])\necho \"M3(P)   | $&id | Vsg=$&vgs | Vth=$&vth | $&vov | Vsd=$&vds | $&vdsat\"\n\n* M5 (PMOS cascode)\nlet id = abs(@m.xota.xm5.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[id])*1e9\nlet vgs = @m.xota.xm5.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vgs]\nlet vth = @m.xota.xm5.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vth]\nlet vov = (abs(vgs)-abs(vth))*1000\nlet vds = abs(@m.xota.xm5.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vds])\nlet vdsat = abs(@m.xota.xm5.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vdsat])\necho \"M5(P)   | $&id | Vsg=$&vgs | Vth=$&vth | $&vov | Vsd=$&vds | $&vdsat\"\n\n* M12\nlet id = abs(@m.xota.xm12.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[id])*1e9\nlet vgs = @m.xota.xm12.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vgs]\nlet vth = @m.xota.xm12.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vth]\nlet vov = (abs(vgs)-abs(vth))*1000\necho \"M12(P)  | $&id | Vsg=$&vgs | Vth=$&vth | $&vov\"\n\n* M7 (NMOS cascode)\nlet id = @m.xota.xm7.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[id]*1e9\nlet vgs = @m.xota.xm7.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vgs]\nlet vth = @m.xota.xm7.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vth]\nlet vov = (vgs-vth)*1000\nlet vds = @m.xota.xm7.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vds]\nlet vdsat = @m.xota.xm7.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vdsat]\necho \"M7      | $&id | $&vgs | $&vth | $&vov | $&vds | $&vdsat\"\n\n* M9\nlet id = @m.xota.xm9.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[id]*1e9\nlet vgs = @m.xota.xm9.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vgs]\nlet vth = @m.xota.xm9.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vth]\nlet vov = (vgs-vth)*1000\nlet vds = @m.xota.xm9.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vds]\nlet vdsat = @m.xota.xm9.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vdsat]\necho \"M9      | $&id | $&vgs | $&vth | $&vov | $&vds | $&vdsat\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"Voltages: Vout=$&v(nout) fold_p=$&v(xota.fold_p) fold_n=$&v(xota.fold_n)\"\necho \"          cas_p=$&v(xota.cas_p) tail=$&v(xota.tail) src7=$&v(xota.src7)\"\necho \"Supply: -i(Vdd) = $&-i(Vdd)\"\nquit\n.endc\n.end\nEOF\n/usr/bin/ngspice -b debug.spice 2>&1 | grep -E \"^DEV|^----|^M|^Volt|^Supp|^    \" | head -20","description":"Test v3 OTA with optimized sizing"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":923,"cache_read_input_tokens":226395,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":923},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"d29dc438-a3a9-413d-9ab0-7f1a28d02391"}
