{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XiK2pjnXYwhJRPa79kZe2W","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The feedback topology is causing asymmetry. M1=835nA but M2=196nA → very unbalanced. fold_p=1.578V but fold_n=1.709V → different voltages for each branch. cas_p is nearly at ground (0.015V)!\n\nThe problem: with Vbcp=0.54V, M5 is now barely on (Vov=80mV). But the left branch (with M1 injecting into fold_p) has a lot of current, while the right branch (with M2 getting less current because vout=0.811 is connected to vinn=vout) has less.\n\n\nThe asymmetry stems from the unity-gain feedback setup—M1's gate sits at 0.9V while M2's gate is tied to vout at 0.811V, causing M1 to draw significantly more current. I should test with symmetric inputs at 0.9V to see if the circuit balances properly with the updated biases. Also, M5's overdrive voltage of 80mV is too low; I need to adjust Vbcp to get M5 to around 150mV overdrive, which means finding the right source-gate voltage.\n\nNow I'm calculating the required Vbcp by working backward from the target overdrive voltage, using the fold voltage from the symmetric simulation to set Vbcp to approximately 0.49V and testing that in the open-loop configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1552,"cache_read_input_tokens":245878,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1552},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"cffeb888-32fa-4fd9-8620-d2b2a99ec540"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XiK2pjnXYwhJRPa79kZe2W","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01AZqRSXyjMCkUpFrpx8iHD6","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/debug.spice << 'EOF'\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd nvdd 0 dc 1.8\nV0 ngnd 0 dc 0\nVbn nbn 0 dc 0.625\nVbcn nbcn 0 dc 0.90\nVbp nbp 0 dc 0.73\nVbcp nbcp 0 dc 0.49\nVinp ninp 0 dc 0.9\nVinn ninn 0 dc 0.9\n\nXota ninp ninn nout nvdd ngnd nbn nbcn nbp nbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL nout 0 10p\n\n.nodeset v(nout)=0.9 v(xota.fold_p)=1.5 v(xota.fold_n)=1.5\n.nodeset v(xota.cas_p)=0.9 v(xota.tail)=0.2 v(xota.src7)=0.15 v(xota.src8)=0.15\n\n.op\n.control\nrun\necho \"Vout = $&v(nout)\"\nlet i11 = @m.xota.xm11.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[id]*1e9\nlet i1 = @m.xota.xm1.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[id]*1e9\nlet i3 = abs(@m.xota.xm3.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[id])*1e9\nlet i12 = abs(@m.xota.xm12.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[id])*1e9\nlet i5 = abs(@m.xota.xm5.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[id])*1e9\nlet i9 = @m.xota.xm9.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[id]*1e9\necho \"M11=$&i11 M1=$&i1 M3=$&i3 M12=$&i12 M5=$&i5 M9=$&i9\"\necho \"\"\nlet vov3 = (abs(@m.xota.xm3.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vgs]) - abs(@m.xota.xm3.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vth]))*1000\nlet vds3 = abs(@m.xota.xm3.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vds])*1000\nlet vdsat3 = abs(@m.xota.xm3.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vdsat])*1000\nlet sat3 = vds3 - vdsat3\necho \"M3: Vov=$&vov3 Vds=$&vds3 Vdsat=$&vdsat3 margin=$&sat3\"\n\nlet vov5 = (abs(@m.xota.xm5.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vgs]) - abs(@m.xota.xm5.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vth]))*1000\nlet vds5 = abs(@m.xota.xm5.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vds])*1000\nlet vdsat5 = abs(@m.xota.xm5.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vdsat])*1000\nlet sat5 = vds5 - vdsat5\necho \"M5: Vov=$&vov5 Vds=$&vds5 Vdsat=$&vdsat5 margin=$&sat5\"\n\nlet vov12 = (abs(@m.xota.xm12.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vgs]) - abs(@m.xota.xm12.msky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8[vth]))*1000\necho \"M12: Vov=$&vov12\"\n\nlet vov1 = (@m.xota.xm1.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vgs] - @m.xota.xm1.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vth])*1000\nlet vov7 = (@m.xota.xm7.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vgs] - @m.xota.xm7.msky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8[vth])*1000\necho \"M1: Vov=$&vov1  M7: Vov=$&vov7\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"fold_p=$&v(xota.fold_p) fold_n=$&v(xota.fold_n) Vout=$&v(nout)\"\necho \"tail=$&v(xota.tail) src7=$&v(xota.src7)\"\nlet isup = abs(-i(Vdd))*1e6\necho \"Supply=$&isup uA\"\nquit\n.endc\n.end\nEOF\n/usr/bin/ngspice -b debug.spice 2>&1 | grep -E \"^Vout|^M|^fold|^tail|^Supp\" | head -15","description":"Test with Vbcp=0.49 in symmetric config"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1552,"cache_read_input_tokens":245878,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1552},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"7af0eff7-1cc3-4d70-a3d2-33a1de61ef6d"}
