{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PGfir8Qv11onMXVFjZnEhL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"At W=0.42u L=20u with Vbp=0.73V (Vsg=1.07V):\n- Id = 25nA\n- Vth = 0.887V\n- Vov = 1.07 - 0.887 = 183mV ✓ (> 150mV)\n- Vdsat = 176mV\n\nL=50u gave the same result as L=20u — probably because these are both in the same model bin.\n\n\nM12 at these dimensions gives me 25nA with the required overdrive voltage, so combining M3's 494nA with M12's 25nA gets me to 519nA per branch, which is right on target. The current distribution works out: M1 takes 250nA and M5 takes the remaining 269nA, matching my total demand. Now I need to verify M5's overdrive voltage at this reduced current level—scaling from the 494nA data point where Vov was 150mV.\n\nAt 269nA, M5's overdrive voltage drops to about 111mV, which is below my 150mV requirement. The problem is that M5 is being starved of current—at Vov=150mV it would want to pass 494nA, but the circuit only supplies 269nA, forcing it to operate at a lower overdrive to match the available current. I need to adjust Vbcp to give M5 the proper gate-source voltage for this reduced current level.\n\nTo achieve Vov=150mV at 269nA, I need to reduce the W/L ratio. Scaling down to W=0.42u L=2u should work—at this geometry with Vov=150mV, the device would pass about 201nA. But since I'm actually pushing 269nA through it, the overdrive voltage will be higher than 150mV to accommodate the extra current.\n\nNow I'm checking whether M5 stays in saturation with these dimensions. At 269nA, Vov comes out to roughly 174mV and Vdsat around 180mV, so I need to verify that the source-drain voltage exceeds the saturation threshold given the bias voltages I'm working with.\n\nLooking at the current mirror formed by M9 and M11, there's a sizing mismatch creating a problem—M9 should mirror 269nA to match M5, but with the current ratio and M11 at 500nA, M9 only sinks 250nA, leaving about 19nA unaccounted for that ends up charging the output node.\n\nTo fix this, I need to adjust M9's W/L ratio to 0.538 so it properly sinks 269nA. I could use W=2.15u L=4u, or go with W=2u L=3.72u, though the latter uses a non-standard length. Let me try the fractional width approach since ngspice should handle it fine.\n\nActually, I should step back and think about what current balance I really need at the output node to keep everything in saturation.\n\nNow I'm laying out the full device dimensions for the revised design, starting with the input pair and current mirror stages. Now I'm working through the biasing conditions for M5, calculating what Vbcp needs to be based on the overdrive voltage and threshold voltage at the given channel length. I'm checking whether M3 stays in saturation by verifying its drain-source voltage exceeds the saturation voltage, which depends on the current demand from the circuit.\n\nFor M7, I'm determining the minimum gate voltage needed to maintain adequate overdrive while accounting for the source voltage set by M9's saturation region, then checking the headroom constraint for the cascode configuration.\n\nNow I'm verifying the output voltage can support the required drain-source voltage across M7 with sufficient margin above saturation, and I've identified from simulation that the bias voltage for M11 should be around 0.585V to achieve the target 500nA current. Let me assemble these constraints and validate the design.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2142,"cache_read_input_tokens":270798,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2142},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"b466bc43-242c-4094-a0ea-59d17d3deb67"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PGfir8Qv11onMXVFjZnEhL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QePEQsgMKnYnH2dq6dLuEM","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/ota_foldcasc.spice << 'EOF'\n* VibroSense Folded-Cascode OTA — SKY130A v6\n* Carefully balanced for Vov constraints at 500nA tail\n\n.subckt ota_foldcasc vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp\n\n* Input Pair (W=0.36u for Vov>50mV at 250nA)\nXM1 fold_p vinp tail vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=0.36u L=1u nf=1\nXM2 fold_n vinn tail vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=0.36u L=1u nf=1\n\n* Tail (500nA)\nXM11 tail vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=4u L=4u nf=1\n\n* PMOS Fold (W=0.42u L=1u, ~494nA at Vov≈150mV)\nXM3  fold_p vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=1u nf=1\nXM4  fold_n vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=1u nf=1\n\n* PMOS Bias Mirrors (very long L: ~25nA, still Vov>150mV)\nXM12 fold_p vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1\nXM13 fold_n vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1\n\n* PMOS Cascode (W=0.42u L=2u, Vov>150mV at ~269nA)\nXM5  cas_p vbcp fold_p vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=2u nf=1\nXM6  vout  vbcp fold_n vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=2u nf=1\n\n* NMOS Cascode (W=0.36u L=1u, Vov>50mV at ~269nA)\nXM7  cas_p vbcn src7 vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=0.36u L=1u nf=1\nXM8  vout  vbcn src8 vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=0.36u L=1u nf=1\n\n* NMOS Current Sources (269nA, ratio 0.538 of M11)\nXM9  src7 vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2.15u L=4u nf=1\nXM10 src8 vbn vss vss sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2.15u L=4u nf=1\n\n.ends ota_foldcasc\nEOF\n\n# Update tb_ota_op.spice biases\ncat > /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_op.spice << 'SPICEFILE'\n* TB07: Operating Point Verification\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\n.param vdd_val = 1.8\n.param vcm_val = 0.9\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc {vdd_val}\n\n* Bias voltages\nVbn  vbn  0 dc 0.585\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.88\nVbp  vbp  0 dc 0.73\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.54\n\n* Symmetric open-loop with output stabilization\nVinp vinp 0 dc {vcm_val}\nVinn vinn 0 dc {vcm_val}\n\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\nRbias vout vmid 100G\nVmid vmid 0 dc {vcm_val}\n\n.op\n.save all\n.control\nrun\n\n* Print all 13 devices in verifier format\nSPICEFILE\n\n# Append the echo block for all devices\npython3 << 'PYEOF'\nnmos_devs = ['m1','m2','m7','m8','m9','m10','m11']\npmos_devs = ['m3','m4','m5','m6','m12','m13']\nparams = ['vgs','vth','vds','vdsat','id','gm','gds']\n\nlines = []\nfor dev in nmos_devs:\n    model = 'sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8'\n    for p in params:\n        lines.append(f'let val = @m.xota.x{dev}.m{model}[{p}]')\n        lines.append(f'echo \"@m.xota.{dev}[{p}] = $&val\"')\n\nfor dev in pmos_devs:\n    model = 'sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8'\n    for p in params:\n        lines.append(f'let val = @m.xota.x{dev}.m{model}[{p}]')\n        lines.append(f'echo \"@m.xota.{dev}[{p}] = $&val\"')\n\nlines.append('echo \"v(vout) = $&v(vout)\"')\nlines.append('echo \"-i(vdd) = $&-i(vdd)\"')\nlines.append('quit')\nlines.append('.endc')\nlines.append('.end')\n\nwith open('/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_op.spice', 'a') as f:\n    f.write('\\n'.join(lines) + '\\n')\nPYEOF\n\necho \"Created OTA v6 and updated testbench\"\npython3 verify_design.py 2>&1 | head -35","description":"Build v6 OTA and run verifier","timeout":180000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2142,"cache_read_input_tokens":270798,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2142},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"8fd8414b-79d1-451d