{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017tRCwSsjhvqr3qV2Svzc1H","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still 147mV. The Vov barely changed (from 146.7 to 147.4). The issue is that M5 Vth is changing as I change Vbcp — DIBL and body effect. The Vth increases as I reduce Vbcp (increase Vsg), partially canceling the Vov increase.\n\nAt Vbcp=0.51: M5 Vsg=1.098V, Vth=0.951V, Vov=147mV\n\n\nAt Vbcp=0.505: M5 Vsg=1.100V, Vth=0.952V, Vov=147mV\n\nThe Vth is increasing by 1mV for every 2mV increase in Vsg, so I'm only getting 1mV more Vov. To reach 150mV, I need another 3mV, which means pushing Vsg up by about 6mV more. That puts Vbcp around 0.499V.\n\nLet me test Vbcp=0.49V.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1312,"cache_read_input_tokens":291812,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1312},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"84dc8f2c-b622-407c-9866-311d27adf9b3"}
