{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016fTwKzToACs11EgNB4LwWF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The AC analysis is not running. In ngspice batch mode, `no data saved` usually means the analysis didn't complete or didn't start. The DC operating point might have failed silently.\n\nActually, looking at the testbench: I have both `.nodeset` and `.ac` in the SPICE deck, no `.control` block. The `.end` is at the end. The issue might be that the `.op` (from nodeset) runs but the `.ac` doesn't execute.\n\nIn ngspice, for batch mode to run `.ac`, there needs to be a `.ac` directive in the deck. Let me verify the file.\n\n\nThe analysis time is essentially zero, suggesting the operating point didn't converge—the 1MΩ stabilization resistor is probably distorting the circuit too much for AC analysis. I should try using unity-gain feedback to set the DC operating point instead, then break the loop for AC with a large inductor as the program suggests.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":161,"cache_read_input_tokens":300182,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":161},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"0503af97-430b-4770-a9cb-7a90997adabe"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016fTwKzToACs11EgNB4LwWF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014JUiVHznWGQ91d2TUvJ92f","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"# Check if OP converges by adding a print\ncat > /tmp/test_ac.spice << 'EOF'\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVbn  vbn  0 dc 0.59\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.88\nVbp  vbp  0 dc 0.73\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.475\n\nVinp vinp 0 dc 0.9 ac 1\nVinn vinn 0 dc 0.9\n\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\nRbias1 vout vmid 1e6\nRbias2 xota.cas_p vmid 1e6\nVmid vmid 0 dc 0.9\n\n.ac dec 100 0.1 1G\n\n.control\nrun\nprint maximum(vdb(vout))\nmeas ac gain_peak MAX vdb(vout)\nmeas ac ugb WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\nmeas ac phase_ugb FIND vp(vout) WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\nmeas ac g1 FIND vdb(vout) AT=1\nmeas ac g10 FIND vdb(vout) AT=10\nmeas ac g100 FIND vdb(vout) AT=100\nquit\n.endc\n.end\nEOF\n/usr/bin/ngspice -b /tmp/test_ac.spice 2>&1 | grep -E \"gain|ugb|phase|g1|g10|g100|maximum|error|Error\" | head -20","description":"Test AC sim with .control block","timeout":180000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":161,"cache_read_input_tokens":300182,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":161},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d800be-0a8d-4fa4-9160-013da436175b","uuid":"38ec2724-bfb4-4b7e-bcec-191541f853cb"}
